def minCostToMoveChips(position):
    evenCount, oddCount = 0, 0
    for i in position:
        if i % 2 == 0:
            evenCount += 1
        else:
            oddCount += 1
    return min(evenCount, oddCount)
```

    The strategy to minimize the cost is to move all the chips to the position where most chips are already placed, either in an even or odd position. In each step, we can move a chip by 2 positions at no cost. So we count the number of chips on even positions and the number of chips on odd positions. The minimum cost is the minimum between the counts of even and odd positioned chips, as we can move the smaller set of chips to the bigger set with minimum operations.

